div1.p: IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE NINTH CIRCUIT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF L.J. URANN FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS} ORDER.

The above entitled cause having come on for hearing in open court in regular session on the 5th day of July, 1905, and the petitioner being in court in person and by his attorney, Vince H. Faben, and the Agent of the State of Massachusetts and the Sheriff of King County being in court and being represented by their attorney and having made return to the Writ of Habeas Corpus heretofor issued herein and the petitioner having taken exceptions to the return as made and having filed his traverse to the return as ammended by permission of the court and the court having ruled upon the challange to the sufficiency of the traverse and having sustained the demurrer of the respondent to the introduction of any testimony upon the part of the petitioner and the petitioner having offered to prove in open court all of the allegations of his petition and the court having sustained the demurrer of the respondent and the court being now fully and sufficiently advised in the premises:-

IT IS THEREFORE ordered and decreed that the relief demanded in said petition for a Writ of Habeas Corpus be denied and that said peititoner be remanded to the custody of L.C. Smith, Sheriff of King County, Washington.
It is further order adjudged and decreed by this court that the petitioner be allowed an appeal herein as provided by law

and that said petitioner, pending said appeal, give bail in the sum of $4,000.00, which said sum is now fixed as bail and supersedeas upon appeal as provided by law and the rules and practice of this court.
Done in open court this 5th day of July, 1905.
IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE NINTH CIRCUIT WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF L.J. URANN FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS
FILED IN THE U.S. Circuit Court, Western Dist. of Washington. ))))))))) A. REEVES AYRES, Clerk A.N. Moor Dep.
Vince H. Faben, 504 Mutual Life Bldg., Seattle, Washington Attorney for Petitioner.
